Description: YouTube is a video hosting and sharing website created in 2005 and acquired by Google in 2006.

Instagram is a photo-sharing service that allows users to share pictures and videos publicly, privately, and through a variety of other social networking platforms. It was acquired by Facebook in 2012.
Periscope is a live video streaming mobile application acquired by Twitter in 2015. In 2016, some of Periscope's features were integrated into the main Twitter platform.
